OL,3,CPeople 'glamourise' migrant hotels,
OL,4,Crefugee tells ITV News
OL,6,F"You might want to get out of that
OL,7,Fparticular situation, but it's not in
OL,8,Fyour own power to do it, it's in the
OL,9,Fpower of the Home Office to make sure
OL,10,Fthat your pending situation is being
OL,11,Famended and you're being moved on to
OL,12,Fthe next level," he said.
OL,14,F"So, I would say to them to pardon us,
OL,15,Fbased on our situations. It is not a
OL,16,Fsituation that we created, we don't
OL,17,Fwant to be part of it, but it
OL,18,Fhappened," he added.
