OL,3,CPeople 'glamourise' migrant hotels,
OL,4,Crefugee tells ITV News
OL,6,FAsylum seekers and their families can
OL,7,Fbe housed in temporary accommodation,
OL,8,Fknown as contingency accommodation, if
OL,9,Fthey are awaiting assessment of their
OL,10,Fclaim or have had a claim approved and
OL,11,Fthere is not enough longer-term
OL,12,Faccommodation available.
OL,14,FWhen there is not enough housing, the
OL,15,FHome Office, which has a legal
OL,16,Fobligation to provide accommodation to
OL,17,Fasylum seekers who would otherwise be
OL,18,Fdestitute, can move people to
OL,19,Falternatives such as hotels and large
OL,20,Fsites, like former military bases.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/21
